<section class="border-b border-[#dce5da] py-16">
    <div class="section-shell grid gap-8 lg:grid-cols-[1fr_0.92fr] lg:items-center">
        <div>
            <p class="font-mono text-sm font-semibold uppercase tracking-normal text-[#0f766e]">Messenger sharing</p>
            <h2 class="mt-3 text-3xl font-semibold tracking-normal text-[#13201d] md:text-4xl">Safe links for messengers</h2>
            <p class="mt-5 text-lg leading-8 text-[#52625d]">
                Send a SecShare link through Telegram, Slack, Discord, or email instead of uploading the raw file there. The file is encrypted before upload, and SecShare never receives the decryption key. Add expiration time and download limits to reduce the risk of long-lived shared files.
            </p>
            <p class="mt-5 rounded-lg border border-[#ead7a7] bg-[#fff8e6] p-4 text-sm leading-6 text-[#6d5521]">
                Anyone with the full link can decrypt the file, so treat it like a temporary secret.
            </p>
        </div>

        <div class="rounded-lg border border-[#dce5da] bg-white p-6 shadow-sm">
            <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-[#13201d]">SecShare does not make messengers magically private.</p>
            <p class="mt-3 text-sm leading-6 text-[#52625d]">
                It makes the shared file encrypted, temporary, and easier to remove.
            </p>
            <div class="mt-6 space-y-3 font-mono text-xs text-[#52625d]">
                <div class="rounded-md border border-[#dce5da] bg-[#f7f8f5] p-3">Telegram -> SecShare link</div>
                <div class="rounded-md border border-[#dce5da] bg-[#f7f8f5] p-3">Slack -> SecShare link</div>
                <div class="rounded-md border border-[#dce5da] bg-[#f7f8f5] p-3">Email -> SecShare link</div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</section>
